         <abstract>
            <p>Let l be a prime number and m a divisor of l - 1. Then the Gauss period ω = ζ + ζ&lt;sup&gt;λ&lt;/sup&gt; + ζ&lt;sup&gt;λ&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; + ⋯ + ζ&lt;sup&gt;λ&lt;sup&gt;m - 1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;, where ζ = e&lt;sup&gt;2π i/l&lt;/sup&gt; and λ is a primitive mth root of unity modulo l, generates a subfield K of Q(ζ) of degree (l - 1)/m. In this paper we study the reciprocal minimal polynomial F&lt;sub&gt;l, m&lt;/sub&gt;(X) = N&lt;sub&gt;K/Q&lt;/sub&gt;(1 - ω X) of ω over Q. It will be shown that for fixed m and every N we have &lt;tex-math&gt;$F_{l, m}(X) \equiv (B_m(X)^l/(1 - mX))^{1/m} (\operatorname{mod} X^N)$&lt;/tex-math&gt; for all but finitely many "exceptional primes" l (depending on m and N), where B&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;(X) ∈ Z[[ X ]] is a power series depending only on m. A method of computation of this set of exceptional primes is presented. The generalization of the results to the case of composite l is also discussed.</p>
          </abstract>
